Morgan Freeman will play Mandela in the new film Clint Eastwood
Despite criticism of the fact that the main roles are played by American actors, South Africans say that the new Hollywood film Invictus - Invaincu will outline the world a lot of things about the country, its struggles and victories.
The story speaks of sport, relations between races and Nelson Mandela.
Morgan Freeman, American actor rewarded the Oscars, embodies the film on the life of Nelson Mandela, tireless fighter against the racist apartheid regime in South Africa and first black president.
Freeman said, that this is a Mandela aged ninety-one years who asked him to embody in the film.
Matt Damon plays an important role.
I told him: "If I must embody, I should be able to see you personally.
The actor seventy-two years old who was awarded a prize for his role in the drama limited dollar baby of Clint Eastwood located in the middle of boxing has, for example, embodied the leader of a movement against slavery itself become a slave, a fictional US president, even God in the film Evan Almighty but never someone still alive and also important for so many people that is Mandela.
The ex-homme State South African was imprisoned 27 years for his hard work in favour of the end of apartheid in South Africa.
He was released in 1990 and became president of the country for four years.
In 1993 he was awarded the Nobel Peace Prize.
Invictus is a Latin word meaning unbeaten and it is the title of a poem by the English author William Ernest Henley published in 1875.
The challenge was to speak like him.
The film tells the true story of the joint efforts of Nelson Mandela and the captain of the South African rugby team François to unify the country. The newly elected President Mandela knows that his country resteencore and always divided racially and economically after apartheid.
It is sure to unite his people through sport and decided to unite the rugby players who are among the outsiders in the world.
The South African team will eventually move in World Cup in 1995.
Freeman has worked for a few years to bring the history of Mandela on screen.
I had no other purpose if not play this role to the closest to the reality, said Freeman.
The biggest challenge for me it was of course to talk like him
The actor said that if he and the international policy were in the same region, it would have tried to meet Mandela, dinner with him, to be behind the scenes before his speech.
The most important thing for him was to shake his hand.
I realized that when I give you my hand, I recover your energy, it is transmitted and I had the impression of how you feel, "he said.
It is important for me to try to become another person.
Matt Damon plays in the film François Pienaar, the captain of a national rugby team in which there is a majority of white players.
The actor said that he had six months to prepare for a role in the harsh environment of rugby.
For him, his first meeting with Pienaar at his home was a great surprise.
I remember when I come to the door of the house, he opened and the first thing I said to Francois Pienaar was: 'I air much greater in the film ".
Despite the differences between the actors and actual models, Invictus under the leadership of director Eastwood received positive view and there is even talk of ambitions for the Oscars.
The film critic Todd McCarthy of the newspaper Daily Variety summarized his appreciation in these words: "This is a very good history, a film very well done."
In the evaluations of films on the site rottentomatoes.com, Invictus received 76 percent of positive feedback.
The mystery of the aura in Norway is resolved: the Russian tested a rocket
There has been a strange luminous phenomenon of unknown origin over Norway.
The Russian Ministry of Defence has recognized that yesterday have tested a rocket intercontinental ballistic not far from the Norwegian border.
The launch has still been a failure and the missile "Bulava" which was originally scheduled to be the pride of the Russian army is gradually becoming the nightmare of Russian generals and Prime Minister Vladimir Putin.
Its presence repeated tests of the rocket has not had the desired effect on the success of test flights.
Most of the time, Bulava has not disappeared, or it is damaged in flight.
The Russian newspapers speak of "Bulava" as the "missile which do not steal"
A missile that do not steal but shining
This 13th test took place at the beginning.
It is only at the end of the flight that there was again damage on the equipment.
This is clearly the engine of the third floor of the rocket that exploded.
This time, "Bulava" is soaring nuclear submarine Dmitrij Donskij which was sailing under the surface of the White Sea.
This type of missile can be fired from a moving boat and submerged
That is why the mysterious light over Norway caused by an unidentified flying object precisely has likely been by a Bulava "defective".
Moreover, the Norwegians have not doubted for a moment that it is a Russian rocket.
The generals argue that this time, we cannot talk absolutely failure.
The first two floors of the rocket have resisted and damage was confined to the third.
In the previous cases, the engines have been failures on the first floor.
Although none of test launches has happened smoothly, the leadership of the Ministry of Defence considers that only six out of thirteen have been failures.
This success rate of almost fifty percent fills the general optimism and they therefore argue that a day "Bulava" fly without problems and that it will prevail even ten nuclei of hypersonic a total weight of 1.15 tonnes.
The legendary Fetissov to 51 years has signed a one-year contract with the CSKA Moscow
The legendary defender Viatcheslav Fetissov will return in a professional match in 51 years.
The former world champion, Olympic champion and holder of the Stanley Cup will help his team of CSKA Moscow in need and will make its entry probablementdéjà during the match on Friday against Petrograd.
