That said, it should not expect the support and tolerance of Democrats.
I have not thought about it and once it will be on the agenda when I shall devote, said since the House to journalists, the Defence Minister Martin Barták, elected government precisely by Democrats.
The Prime Minister Fischer has soared in the afternoon for a debate of the European Council in Brussels.
The ODS has backtracked at the request of the Prime Minister.
Nečas stressed at the same time that the ODS would probably have voted on Wednesday against the amended budget if he had not specifically asked Members Democrats to allow the vote on the budget.
We do not have the feeling of being orphans, it is no small children, he responded to the question of whether the ODS had not suffered accusations from the President of the Party in the House or in the country during the negotiation of the budget.
I have not noticed that my vote would have been lacking.
I already knew when I renounced my mandate that what would follow in the coming months would be a bolchévisation of the House and destruction of all that was positive, reacted Topolánek in person.
According to the new schedules of the ČD there will be fewer trains for the same charges.
The Czech railways will remove or limit from 13 December some express trains or regional less responsible and will instead some others.
The total coverage of transport will fall on the day of entry into force of the new schedule of two percent compared to today.
Most of the charges will not change, including the basic rates and the reduced rate.
For example, the inhabitants of the region in Ostrava who will have more connections to the capital, the Railways will add a rowing pendolino.
On the contrary, an express will cease to serve Bratislava.
There will also be less fast trains on the line Prague - Písek - České Budějovice, the direct line Prague - Letohrad will be drastically reduced.
At the regional level, the largest decline in transportation is the region of Hradec Králové eight percent in total, however Prague and its environs can rejoice an increase.
Two night trains on the line Prague - Tábor - České Budějovice are also cancelled and the movement of some express trains on the line Prague - Písek - České Budějovice is reduced to only a few days in the week.
Among the biggest changes, we can see the introduction of a new direct line of Milovice in Prague: for the moment the inhabitants of Milovice must change to Lysá nad Labem.
It is the fifteenth line of the commuter system Esko, whose opening is possible thanks to the completion of the electrification of the line between Lysá nad Labem and Milovice.
The lines distant to the capital will have their final destination at the main station in Prague (Praha Hlavní nádraží).
The ČD will introduce more lines HC Pendolino between Prague and Ostrava and trains to Šumperk / Jeseník will leave by intervals of two hours.
Travellers can no longer take the Pendolino to Bratislava from 13 December.
The bill this year for the regional railways: 200 million kroner.
The express trains are ordered and paid by the Ministry of Transport and will pay the Railways next year in all four billion kroner to settle losses visible, or the same amount as this year. The regional trains are ordered by the regions who will pay for their by a total of eight billion next year, knowing that the state will be up to almost three billion.
This year the regional trains are 200 million more expensive.
The railways have newly signed a contract for ten years, until now the duration was always a year.
The Railways appreciate the system, which also explains that they have not resorted to a price increase of the vast majority of tickets.
The changes will affect only tickets a day ČD Net and notes Internet at reduced prices eLiška.
For travellers without a map of reduction, the price of ČD Net increase from 450 to 600 crowns.
The price of eLiška newly will depend on the journey, whereas previously it was valid between the towns of a region to choice and was at a single rate of 160 crowns.
The Filipino rebels still hold more than 50 people, children have been released
The rebels have kidnapped today 75 people in the southern Philippines, including some students of a primary school and their teachers.
It is the AFP Agency who informed, but who spoke to the origin of 65 hostages only.
The 17 children were released after eight hours, as well as one of the teachers.
The hostage-taking took place in the province of Agusan del Sur.
It is reported that about 19 rebels have used the hostages as human shields during a flight with the police.
The local negotiators are trying to find an agreement for the release of the remaining hostages.
According to the AFP Agency, the rebels belong to the New People's Army (NPA), which is the armed wing of the Communist Party of the Philippines (CPP).
According to the AFP agency, the police initially pursued the kidnappers following violence caused during a settling of accounts between two family clans.
Martial law was declared in the province of Maguindanao in the southern Philippines because of a recent massacre during which 57 people were killed.
Among the victims of the massacre of 23 November election related to the administration of the Governor there avait30 journalists.
The governor of the province of the southern Philippines was arrested on suspicion of involvement in the massacre, as well as his father Andal Ampatuan, patriarch of the lineage of influential Ampatuan.
The island Mindanao also includes Muslim separatists assets.
