But a representative of the Pakistani secret services has been informed of the case said Saturday that Saifullah had failed to convince the Al-Qaida commanders that these men were not involved in the conspiracy of the CIA to infiltrate the terrorist network.
As a result, they have been isolated for days in the eastern city of Sargodha, far from the mountains banned from northeast become a haven for terrorism.
