The prison guards' unions called Friday for "general mobilization" to demand the payment by the end of year holidays bonuses and overtime which payment has been deferred to January for budgetary reasons.
(2nd FO-pénitentiaire union of supervisors) asked the staff who will not be in service to demonstrate Tuesday morning in prisons and the "block" to "denounce the theft of their due."
The CGT-pénitentiaire (3rd union of the profession) calls on them to "meet in general assemblies in the various prisons for a strong turnout" as "shameful and unacceptable" the non-payment in December "overtime, bonuses nights, Sundays and holidays" worked in October.
