The court of Nanterre decided Friday to judge the artist François-Marie Banier, to determine if, as the acknowledges the daughter of the billionaire Liliane Bettencourt, it has benefited from a state of weakness of the octogenarian to rob a portion of his fortune.
The photographer for 62 years, known for its photos of stars, will be judged on 15 and 16 April 2010 for abuse of weakness, a crime punishable by a maximum sentence of three years imprisonment and 375.000 fine of €.
This decision means that there will be a trial in this case worthy of a saga on one of the richest families of France, in which a mother and daughter tear while taking the reins of the L'Oreal cosmetics empire.
But the 15th criminal Chamber also ordered that a medical expertise of Liliane Bettencourt, aged 87 years, should be carried out collectively by three doctors.
The heir and main shareholder of the L'Oreal has always refused to submit to such a review, at least not in the conditions proposed by the prosecutor of Nanterre during the investigation.
Doctors appointed Friday will submit a report before March 10, 2010 in particular if Liliane Bettencourt saying could find themselves in a state of weakness and what periods.
I think it will.
I am going to talk about it, said at the exit of the hearing, counsel for Mrs Bettencourt, Mr. Georges Kiejman.
For its part, counsel for Françoise Bettencourt-Meyers, Mr. Olivier Metzner, welcomed the decision of the court.
This is an excellent new (...) The expertise will show that he (Mr Banier) has handled this elderly lady that we must protect, he said.
For the last two years, the only daughter of Liliane Bettencourt has committed criminal prosecutions against François-Marie Banier, photographer and journeyman entertainer, which it accuses of having benefited for years from the weakness of his mother to obtain a billion euros of donations, in the form of cheques, contracts of life insurance or tables of masters.
For its part, Liliane Bettencourt has always denied having been manipulated by the photographer, which it sees as a long-time friend.
While the court should examine the admissibility of the action taken by Ms. Bettencourt-Meyers, arguments from lawyers have sometimes turned into a large family unpacking Friday.
Thus, counsel Liliane Bettencourt has reported three letters sent by his client (in 1999, 2003 and 2005) to his notary, in which she said wary of the husband of Françoise Bettencourt-Meyers.
In the letter dated 2003, Liliane Bettencourt added, according to the lawyer: "could you explain to my daughter that I wrote to Banier once, twice a day for 15 years.
Françoise, I have never been able to talk to him since his marriage ".
For its part, the prosecutor in Nanterre again felt that the complainant was not admissible to act, particularly as a guardianship judge refused in recent days to grant his request to open a procedure of judicial protection for his mother.
Liliane Bettencourt "has full capacity to act in court, it is not under protection and has no guardian.
No one else has to act in his place, "said the representative of the public prosecutor, Marie-Chrsitine Daubigney.
The court has finally decided that it would decide once the trial will be held on the admissibility of Ms. Bettencourt-Meyers.
Revolution managerial or end of economic intelligence?
If nothing changes in the governance of large French companies, our struggle for the development of the economic intelligence will have been in vain …
For more than a decade, the attitude of the management of big business vis-à-vis its employees, said the business position vis-à-vis consumers before the revolution marketing: It is to join the staff to "values" determined from above as it was once, to impose the consumer products designed by technicians of the plant.
By putting the customer at the heart of the company, the revolution has handed the marketing strategies of conquest of markets at the place... although the authoritarian temptation to impose products disconnected factors preferences of customers back regularly!
A demobilization of employees can lead to a deadly demoralization.
The suicides at France Telecom, PSA and Renault are only the tip of a much more general phenomenon that affects in particular.
This demobilization seriously undermines the development of all intellectual functions of the company, including the R & D and, more importantly, the economic intelligence.
Indeed, the IE "requires all stakeholders (...) a proactive approach and a forward-looking vision"; it requires on the part of employees a commitment that the authoritarian management revenue thwart completely.
That is why we call for a managerial revolution that would put the staff at the centre of the concerns of the business as the client.
The usefulness any relative of opinion surveys internal
The internal opinion surveys as the questionnaire submitted by Orange to its salariés- will encourage this revolution in the managerial practices?
Unfortunately, I fear not.
- firstly because I could see that, faced with a new situation, any structure in the end, after many detours, priority ... what it has always done.!
- Secondly, because authoritarianism - pathologies of pouvoir- increases in proportion to the importance of its own failures.
- Finally, because most of the leaders have a simplistic view of human behaviour.
From the major engineering schools, they have a mechanistic interpretation of psychology.
They adopt, by intellectual comfort, the old theory Behavioriste, recently revived by the "Neuroscience" and widely disseminated, without their knowledge, by the institutes and the media.
Thus, suggesting that it is possible to handle the "levers" (sic) the commitment of executives, a recent survey by Ipsos published in Le Figaro.fr conforte-t-elle the leaders in a mechanistic governance posture, unsuited to today's world.
Identify and measure the factors of mobilization
On the contrary, the managerial revolution necessary for the proper functioning of modern enterprises, to adopt a vision of human behaviour.
It is to integrate, in any reasoning or practice of governance, a fundamental observation: For employees, the commitment to the company is possible only if it is clear as a means of achieving a part of their dreams, their ambitions, their projects.
Currently, only studies from the Analysis motifonctionnelle adopt this design of the motivations of employees.
These studies have shown that they consider their business based on a predetermined doxa which allows them through their image of the company, to assess what it offers them to achieve their life projects.
Through the identification and the extent of these factors of mobilization, business leaders can control, predict and anticipate their "social performance" and submit their management of human resources "to the place".
They create a breeding ground for joint development of a robust economic intelligence and effective.
