The chain of American television CNBC reported in a story that Citigroup was also planning to repay the aid received.
The banking institutions seek to get rid of restrictions, which accompanied the acceptance of money, such as the limitation of bonuses awarded to the officer and the Regulation of higher costs.
The Bank of Americaa launched a capital increase through the sale of securities from investors who has reported $19 billion of fresh money.
The rest of the money comes from the coffers of the bank that are met through the sale of several branches of other sectors.
