The bank had assumed its capacity by buying the investment bank Merrill Lynch at the height of the financial turmoil.
The Citigroup also plans to get money on the financial markets to liberate themselves from the guardianship of the State.
The U.S. bank could launch as early as Thursday a capital increase of 20 billion, reported the chain CNBC, quoting the banking community.
The spokesman of Citigroup did not wish to comment on this information.
