The promise of FonPeek
Peek is extremely limited, it is a device that allows only to watch his e-mail, without offering the possibility of even see some type of attachments or surf the Internet.
It took advantage of its five minutes of fame in the United States, when Time magazine the designated as one of the products of the year.
In truth, it is more difficult to see in the street, but the idea seems interesting, especially for young people.
Unlike Smartphones, Peek offers a price and a monthly subscription very low, less than half of what it costs, for example, the subscription data of the iPhone.
Given its success, the company launched two new devices: one designed exclusively for Twitter, the other with a free service data for life, for six times more expensive than the Peek.
FonPeek, presented yesterday at the event The Web, is the European version of the invention and its third incarnation.
It is also limited its grand-frère American, but includes a surprise.
The price of its monthly subscription, about 12 euros, includes the roaming across Europe.
Those who travel with a Smartphone already know what it means not to data when it crosses a border or seek desperately a cafeteria on the Wi-Fi (or a connection of Fon) to consult his mail.
The idea of a roaming at a fixed price is incredibly attractive and it is a long time that it should operate.
Indeed, some operators have special agreements and travel options, but as far as I am concerned, I would need to have a thesis in physics for the understanding and good glasses to read the small print.
The repeated reminders to the European Commission to propose roaming fees affordable across Europe have had a barely perceptible.
Outside his country of origin, we hesitate to use the data, and it was not wrong.
