75% of working mothers have had problems because of their maternity
Discrimination at work has increased in recent years, especially for women of younger generations who want to be mothers.
This shows the study "Fertility and professional career women in Spain," conducted by the CSIC in collaboration with the Instituto de la Mujer.
The survey, conducted on 9 737 women 15 to 75 years, leaves no room for doubt: 75 percent of working mothers saw their professional career limited because of motherhood.
The study indicates that there are many differences about the beginning of life as a couple and the number of children, if the woman works or not and the type of job.
Those who do not work outside the home, work part-time or have a stable work shortly, are earlier in couple, have their first pregnancy earlier and have more children.
In contrast, women with a stable job, mainly in the public sector, postpone the entry in the relationship and the first pregnancy, and have fewer children.
Women aged between 35 and 49 with a fixed work have their first child, on average, 3.7 years after being installed as a couple. This figure rises to 4.1 among those working in the public sector. "These data show that women with a stable job needed more time in their lives for it, which led to push the union and the arrival of children.
In addition, the type of employment exercised influence largely motherhood, but less the start date of common life, "said the researcher of the CSIC Margarita Delgado.
The level of education is another factor that widening the gap in the age of marriage of women and their first child.
According to the survey, the higher the level of training, the more they marry and have their first child later.
The difference is also among women of the same generation.
For example, in the group aged between 35 and 49 years, those who have elementary and higher were respectively mothers for the first time to 25.1 and 32.1 years on average.
"Another disctinction is also among women, according to their level of education.
While those who took elementary school marry and have their first child before finding a stable job, those with studies of average level or higher reverse this programme and give priority to achieve a stable work as a precondition to marriage and the arrival of a child, "said Mrs Delgado.
