On Dorothy Parker: "One day she began to its knees and prayed:" Dear God, I beg you to do that I ever write as a woman. "
On Joseph Conrad: "On his tomb were engraved worms Spenser:" Sleep after the effort, / after the storm the port, / the rest after the war, / after life, tired death delights. "
On Virginia Wolf: "In its baggage she was carrying its depression.
Her husband accepted very normally she tell him that Edward VII épiait between the azalées or that the birds singing in Greek.
It has never seen a man as patient and lover of a névrosée whose literary talent exceeded the madness. "
