A cowardly aggression
Last week, my mother, who was about 70 years old, was walking in our neighbourhood of the city of Fuenlabrada, when a group of young people between 15 and 18 years spent beside her and our dog, a sang-mélé, saved from the APS and not weighing more than kg, and without saying a word, they kicked two assenèrent who left the dog seriously injured.
Our indignation is immense because we do not see what is fun to attack a defenceless animal small free which, moreover, was on a leash.
Add to this the indignation of a woman who was walking quietly and who, when she injuria these individuals, came to fear for her physical integrity, since a énergumène which attack an animal is capable of doing the same thing to a woman, a child, a man or, ultimately, anyone lower than him.
The episode took place at around 5 p.m., Tuesday as another in a usually quiet.
The dog has gémi throughout the day.
Of course, we have filed a complaint to the police station in the neighborhood although we doubt that this serves to much, and not to touch the sensibilities, we just want to clarify that the cowardly murderers were Spanish.
The indignation has led us to denounce this fact.
We do not understand what is happening in young people to find amusing to mistreat free a defenceless animal which gives us the love, friendship and our company.
We do not know where is the good education and respect for animals and people.
Michelin and Fesvial, sets for the helmet
The tyre manufacturer Michelin, in collaboration with the Spanish Foundation for Traffic Safety (Fesvial), has launched a campaign to encourage the wearing of helmets, mainly among the young, as reported today the two structures.
This initiative aims to raise awareness of the importance of the helmet, since it is the only element of protection to avoid injuries to the head, or even death, in case of an accident in two wheels.
Michelin said that this campaign was in line with his commitment to road safety, which "goes beyond the design and manufacture of products always safer" and said she contributed to this objective by other actions to educational and informative.
This new campaign to encourage the helmet two wheels, under the motto "To be or not to be," will include a first phase during which posters will be distributed in more than 500 garages motorcycles, in order to ensure the widest possible dissemination.
Finally, Michelin has stressed that road safety "is a constant concern" for the company, because as a manufacturer of tyres for two-wheeled vehicles, one of its main objectives is to develop products always safer.
The sale of light commercial vehicles is
After almost two years, the market for light commercial vehicles is beginning to see some light at the end of the tunnel.
The 9 425 vehicles registered in November in Spain represent an increase of 12.6% compared to 2008 and, more importantly, they represent the first increase after 22 consecutive months of decline, according to figures from the union of manufacturers Anfac and Ganvam, the dealers.
It is, however, to qualify the good news, since the reference for the comparison, the month of November 2008, was particularly bad, with a decrease of 60% compared to the previous year.
As a result, despite the rebound last month, registrations accumulated during those 11 months are 40% below those of the previous year.
Since January, if you add up all vehicles in the category of light commercial vehicles (derived from passenger cars, pickups, vans, light vans and trucks to lightweight chassis) 95 have been sold.
The dark clouds that affect their application are not dispelled. In effect, although they are also purchased by individuals, most purchases are made by small or medium-sized enterprises, which pay in almost 100% of cases through an external funding.
Thus, in addition to the restrictions implied by the limitation of bank loans, it must add other factors such as the increase in the unemployment rate or the persistence of the poor economic climate.
Faced with this situation and the difference of passenger vehicles, the aid to the purchase of the 2000E have little used.
In addition to individuals, the self-employed and SMEs wishing to acquire a light commercial vehicle of less than 3.5 tonnes with a level of CO2 emissions that does not exceed 160 grams per kilometre, can also benefit, but the number of operations speaks for itself.
Yesterday, in Ganvam, it recalled again the need for the administration to pay particular attention to these vehicles and also to industrial vehicles (trucks and buses).
The dealers' association provides a year 2010 similar to the one that ends, for which it calculates a drop in sales (passenger vehicles and 4x4) of 19%.
The emergency braking is now mandatory
As has occurred with the ABS brake system and as this will take place with the ESP stability control systems, the emergency brake assistance will be a compulsory element on European cars.
They are already mandatory on passenger cars and light commercial vehicles newly registered, while for the rest of the vehicles a waiting period has been set until the end of February 2011.
The measure, imposed by the European Union, aims to strengthen the protection of pedestrians, even if, by its mode of action, it can also help prevent many rear shocks.
The assistant emergency braking is increasing the pressure on the brakes in urgent cases detected by the system through the kick given by the driver.
But it does not always maintained the pressure until the end.
According to a study conducted by the manufacturer of components for cars Bosch, a third of the drivers involved in an accident had not been able to support on the brake before the collision, and half of them had not benefited from its full force.
Up to 1 100 accidents
The intervention of the aid, in revancha, requires the maximum of the brake system, reducing the distance that the car needs to stop.
According to a study of the EU, if all cars were equipped with this type of elements, up to 1 100 fatal accidents in which pedestrians are involved could be avoided each year.
This reduction would be even more important with the popularization of so-called intelligent emergency braking systems: It calculates that a disaster on four with casualties would be avoided.
In this case, the vehicle is equipped with a system which, thanks to a radar or a camera, detects obstacles and warns the driver, in addition to act slightly on the brakes.
If the driver reacts, it means increasing the pressure on the pedal, if necessary.
If it does not react, and although the collision is inevitable, the device is the maximum effort on the brakes in order to minimize the damage.
