While workers at the Opel factory in Figueruelas (Zaragoza) have been warned by Nick Reilly, the new president of General Motors (GM) Europe, that the production of the new Meriva would be launched during the first week of April – probably the 8 – after Javier Ortega, the American manufacturer has warned that it will need more time to conclude the contingency plan of Opel.
