At the wheel of the Porsche Boxster Spyder
To design their last and valuable jewelry, engineers are parties of the Porsche BOXSTER S and succeeded to the thinning of nothing less than 80 kilos, leaving the balance to only 1 275 kilograms.
This has led to happen, first, the automatic roof which has been replaced by a static roof manual, to reduce 21 kilos, use of aluminum doors as the WG3, other 15 kilos of less, to remove the air conditioner, 13 kilos, to reduce the gas tank of 64 54 litres, 7 kilos of earned, climbing bacquets sport, still 12 kilos, and with light tires of 19 inches, five kilos.
Finally, they have renounced the audio system CDR-30, earning six other kilograms and have replaced the poignéesdes by door handles in tissues, saving the kilo remaining.
Although the model also exists with the box PDK double clutch, the test was carried out on a model to manual transmission of six speeds, mainly on secondary roads in California, in the mountains, with particularly tortuous turns.
His behaviour cannot be described as beyond reproach.
The weight does not prevent the car to drive on the ground with aplomb.
On the contrary: it was a long time that we had not tested a model as small and light, at the same time, guarantees of security in turns, including at high speed.
It is a small athlete, able to heat its musclesà small speed for the time, until we ask of sprinter, to curb, recover and grow again its engine...
It is out what we wanted. Through his leadership, communicative also specifies that the car will do what will indicate our hands on the steering wheel.
And it will do so with surgical precision.
His engine at will
The sound of his V6 boxer, with 320 horses (10 more than the Boxster S) is particularly successful and can be strengthened with the option "sport" or through a system that changes the roar of the engine, already used on the Panamera.
The ability of acceleration is brutal, either to the judgment or during recoveries.
The suspensions are firm, but not harsh or uncomfortable.
The roads that we have travelled with the Boyxster Spyder was quite damaged, but the car was well managed potholes.
The electronic assistants were barely act of presence on the entire journey, while some turns we found the ice in the morning and gravels, later in the morning.
Ultimately, a car ultralégère, more entertaining to drive and which is much more than a simple change of the Boxster S.
The car will be put for sale in February 2010, at a price of 70 831 euros.
