How much should you be paid according to your Facebook profile?
Users of Facebook may know the salary they deserve their profile, thanks to a new application of Trovit, the search engine with the largest number of real estate paper, employment and vehicles in Spain.
The tool "How should you be paid?" calculates the salaries of users from more than 140 000 job opportunities available Trovit in Spain, from a form available on Facebook, where you have to register your profession, your years of experience, your age and the city where you want to work.
For a week that the application works, the search engine has detected that, in general, the Spanish worker "feels poorly paid," explained in a news release the products of Trovit, Albert Ribera.
According to the data available from its trovità search engines in the United Kingdom and France, the Spanish are less well paid.
A British computer programmer collects 45 226 euros annual gross and a French, 31 059, while a Spanish receives 24 000 euros.
Similarly, a driver perceives 34 247 euros annual gross in England, 25 751 in France and 16 420 in Spain.
According to trovit, the lowest paid in Spain is that of server, with 11 592 Euros annual net, followed by the seller, with 14 725 euros, and that of worker, with 15 667 euros.
The most sought-after jobs on the Internet during the past three months are the driver, the part-time jobs and social worker.
Brazil sets a date for the departure of Zelaya
The Brazilian government has set a deadline for the stay of Manuel Zelaya in its embassy in Tegucigalpa.
The deposed president will abandon the diplomatic legation no later than January 27, 2010, the date of the official end of its mandate.
Francisco Catunda, chargé d ’ affaires of the Embassy of Brazil in the capital of Honduras, confirmed to TV Globo that "Mel" knows that he must leave the embassy, where he has refugee since 21 September, before that date.
"It is aware that he must leave on 27 January, at the end of its mandate, it must seek another destination."
The chain has also cited the former agent, who has confirmed its intention that leave the embassy before the end of the deadline established: "My position is to leave as soon as possible, logically, with the support of the Brazilian government," Zelaya said by telephone.
After the elections of 29 November (during which Porfirio Lobo was elected), Zelaya assured that he would remain in the embassy of Brazil until January.
However, the same week, he tried to seek refuge in Brazil.
The operation ultimately failed, since Zelaya refused the condition of exiled policy that would impose the de facto government headed by Roberto Micheletti.
Thank you very much
After days roses since last spring, during which the asset inflation was the dominant note on the markets, the uncertainty there arises again, which is not surprising since it is their natural state, in an environment where agents make decisions on a future inherently uncertain.
The remedy used by central banks to stabilise the markets has been to monetize the debt by the direct purchase of assets and indirectly providing ample liquidity at rates close to zero, so that financial institutions buy assets to mobilize.
Central banks have already confirmed that the direct purchases of assets were virtually finalized and, without jeopardising their political maverick of liquidity, begin to put a bit of sand in the wheels, as did the ECB, with their award to a year in the next week.
Therefore, investors doubt the ability of the global economy to maintain an economic recovery measures heterodox and we are seeing a reversal of the reduction of risk premiums.
The volatility of scholarships and variances business obligations are growing again, although they remain very distant occultism levels they have achieved at the beginning of the year.
States were forced to socialize the risk private and public debt is again affected.
There is again a flight to quality and the United States, Japan and Germany were the shelters selected by investors, causing an increase of differences between the countries of the euro zone and Germany.
Spain has been barely affected by this episode of instability, but then Standard & Poor its threatened a new downward revision of the qualification of the Kingdom of Spain.
On the other hand, a little uncertainty is not bad to silence the defenders of moral hazard, who tried to provoke a new case of conscience in lesresponsables of global economic policy that had hampered the destructive effects of limiting the credit derivatives on the destruction of employment, whereas what we should do is declare a new day of Thanksgiving.
However, the situation of Dubai resembles a tribal fight between the sheikhs to restore its place in power in the emirates and we have already seen the case of Greece.
A government that conceals a public deficit, elections, and a new government who discovers the pot in roses.
Prodi did in Italy after Berlusconi and Socrates in Portugal after Durão Barroso.
It would be perfectly irrational that Ecofin saves Hungary a breach of its external payments at the beginning of the year and allow a member country of the euro area not to meet its commitments.
What makes sense is that the Ecofin has prompted the Greek government to transparency and makes its citizens share the need for extraordinary measures to maintain the stability of its public finances.
If, as we hope, we are faced with an episode of standardisation of risk premiums transitional, after some excesses in high positions, this would be predictable.
In the case of Spain, as our differences of the public debt rises to the extent of the obligations of European companies, nousn' not have to worry.
If the European gap decreased and that ours continued to increase, it would be a risk idiosyncratic Spanish.
The case Standard & Poor's is an anecdote. When our predictors oblige most services of studies to anticipate their models of recovery and to revise upwards their forecasts for 2011, with the OECD and the European Commission, returning to the office with a Japanese model pourl' Spanish economy, it does not bode much hope for their warning.
Again, this has the air of an excellent opportunity to buy assets Spanish, even if for the moment "caution is the mother of safety".
Sectors connected
The chairman of Iberdrola, Ignacio Sánchez Galán, was the first to intervene yesterday, before the subcommittee of the Congress of Deputies, where is discussed these days the energy strategy of Spain for the next two decades.
After his speech, which was followed by the President of Gas Natural-Fenosa, Rafael Villaseca, Mr Galán has outlined for the press that he had raised before the Subcommittee, in camera.
For the president of Iberdrola, Spain needs to invest 50 000 million until 2020 and 60 000 million more between that date and 2030, where the nuclear power plants in operation would remain open.
If this is not the case, the necessary investments do not amount to 60 000 million but to 95,000.
By contrast, Iberdola considers that for the next decade, investments should not be used to increase production capacity, but the distribution networks and international interconnections.
From 2020, the question is changing, and it will increase the power.
His gamble focuses on the central gas to coal, with mechanisms for recovery of carbon dioxide and, above all, on renewable energy.
In this area, it considers that 18,000 MW of more are needed, with other "energy of support".
Galán, who believes that the draft law a sustainable economy that the government has just approved is in line with what his company, did not want to attack the royal decree aimed to encourage the use of coal, which contradicts the policies to combat global warming.
According to him, there was "a clear long-term bet" in this sense, despite the measures "one-off" as described the chairman of Iberdrola.
Nevertheless, Galán believes that decisions to invest, although they are in the long term, should begin to be taken, because they are some time before reaching maturity and a stable pay framework is needed to address them.
Ferrovial wins the market handling of Aer Lingus in ten airports
The Swiss company Swissport, a subsidiary of Ferrovial for airport services on earth, will play the role of a privileged partner of the Irish airline Aer Lingus, for freight services, in ten European airports where it is present.
Paris, London, Frankfurt and Brussels are part of the most important.
The agreement, whose economic terms have not been disclosed, has a duration of five years.
On the other hand, Ferrovial, the Junta de Castilla-La Mancha and the University of Alcalá de Henares yesterday signed a protocol for collaboration to create the Centre innovation of intelligent infrastructure.
The alliance provides an investment of 20 million until 2012, 50% will come from Ferrovial.
One of the tasks of the centre will conduct research on energy efficiency on motorways and airports.
