The Australian market infrastructure promises of major projects and privatisation, but enter represents a great difficulty, if not through the acquisition of a local construction company.
A strategy that followed the companies Hochtief and Bilfinger, already mentioned, in addition to their Asian references, and which is still a step not validated for the Spanish giants of the sector.
ACS has barely win a place on the market by its 30 percent stake in Hochtief, owner of Leighton.
Assets millionaires
Acciona put on a geographical area of the utmost importance for the sector, on which it already has a large presence through its energy supplier and activity in the area of desalination.
Among other assets, it has the largest wind farm, the Waubra (192 MW) in Victoria, and leads the consolidation of companies responsible for building and managing the dessalinisateur in Adelaide, with a budget of 700 million.
It now intends to consolidate these two areas and take advantage of synergies to enter the markets of the construction and management of infrastructure.
The underground route, promoted by the Office of the infrastructure of the city of Brisbane and the Northern Link (north), is called upon to connect the highway to the Toowong western peripheral route to Kelvin Grove (see map), by 4 kilometres of tunnel. It is the largest existing project to reduce traffic congestion in Brisbane.
The timetable set by the administration indicates that the auction will take place during the summer of 2010 and that the work will begin in December of next year.
Despite the fact that this road toll will be open to traffic late 2014, it is not anticipated that the site is completed before 2016.
The tunnel has begun to be designed in 2005.
It will include two times two lanes, an electronic toll system and a complex ventilation system.
The Queensland Government will provide 500 million Australian dollars (308 million euros) for its funding.
Brisbane already provides work to Hochtief
Australia continues to be widely bring Hochtief, who mentioned yesterday obtaining a contract with the government estimated at 154 million.
The company owned by ACS will equip, through its local subsidiary Leighton, the infrastructure of the national network broadband fiber optic.
This intervention will enable 400 000 people to have quick access to the Internet and provide work for the German company for 18 months.
On the other hand, the company has given the construction of the tower King George, 27 floors, in the city of Brisbane. The work has not yet started and Hochtief concluded the sale to 129 million.
In the United Kingdom, specifically in Manchester, she will share with Laing O'Rourke construction and management of two school groups for 25 years.
The initial investment will be 75 million euros.
FCC is adjudiquer a tunnel in Slovenia for 64 million
FCC, through its subsidiary Alpine, is Adjudiquer the construction of a tunnel 2.1 km long for a motorway in Slovenia, for an amount of EUR 64.5 million.
The company has achieved this contract a few days after the busy work of expansion of the tunnel Bosruck (Austria), for a total of 130 million.
Alpine consolidates its experience in the construction of tunnels.
The launch of the site is scheduled for early 2010 and its implementation will take 32 months.
Sra. Rushmore is adjudiquer advertising of Renfe
Renfe has left the services of advertising and marketing of these two years to the agency SRA. Rushmore, for a budget of around three million euros per year, said the rail operator.
The contract mentioned the possibility of two extensions of 12 months each. Sra. Rushmore was chosen from among 16 agencies that are presented to the tender organised by Renfe, of which four were finalists, including TBWA who was responsible for the creativity during the past three years.
From now on, Sra. Rushmore will be responsible for the design and production of the campaigns.
A fine of 63 million to France Telecom to curb competition
The French competition regulator imposed a fine of 63 million euros to France Telecom for its anti-competitive conduct in the Caribbean region belonging to the country.
According to this institution, the operator has limited competition in the fixed and mobile telephony by signing exclusive agreements, tariffs and loyalty programs to consumers in the margins of the regulation.
With this sanction, the former French monopoly and even state company, accumulates over 450 million euros in fines since 1994, because of the obstacles it puts its competitors.
The sanction imposed yesterday has been increased because the authority which ensures competition considers that France Telecom has committed similar offences in the past and that it is therefore repeat offender.
A shop applications
On the other hand, the mobile phone subsidiary of the French company has followed the wake of other operators and opened a shop of Internet applications, with the objective of increasing revenue from outside the transmission of voice.
Initially, the shop applications of Orange will be active in France and the United Kingdom.
It will wait until 2010 for that it happens in other countries such as Spain.
Their participation in the Champions League reported 476.4 million to Real Madrid and Barça since its creation
The Champions League has become a source of income for clubs, since its birth in 1992.
Indeed, the Real Madrid and F.C. Barcelona have won 467,4 million, which puts them in third and fifth position of clubs who have pocketed the most money in this competition.
The Manchester United is at the top of the list.
The Manchester United is at the top of the list.
Win the UEFA Champions League does not only the glory. It is also one of the main sources of income of big clubs.
Indeed, the competition has allocated 5 million to 105 teams (including 12 Spanish) who participated in the event since the establishment of the tournament, during the 1992-93 season, according to information from Uefa.
The Real Madrid and F.C. Barcelona have been well served in this distribution.
The club was the third of the continent to receive the most money for his participation, and the only one, with the A.C. Milan, has won three times the trophy.
The Catalan club, current taking the title and last winner of the old European Cup in 1992, is fifth on the list.
At the top of the list are the Manchester United and Bayern Munich, the two teams which, moreover, have charged the more money for their participation in the last Champions League.
And that, although they have lost before the Barça.
On the other hand, Spain is only the third country, in the money reported by the Champions League, although it has won more titles than any other (five, while Italy has won four, England three and Germany two).
Distribution
This apparent paradox is explained by the complex procedure of allocation of money applied by UEFA.
For this year, the body chaired by Michel Platini plans to earn 1 090 million through to the Champions League.
Of this amount, UEFA will devote 413,1 million fixed payments: each of the 20 clubs who participated in the classification matches (including the Atlético Madrid) received 2,1 million.
In addition, those who have managed to participate have received 3.8 million just to be there, more than 550 00 euros for each match.
There is also a bonus in the event of victory (800 000 euros) and equality (400 000 for each team). Those who arrive in huitièmes of final receive three million each, the eight teams who arrive in a quarter-final reçoivent3, 3 million.
The last four teams will each receive 4 million.
And the champion will win 9 million, the 5.2 received by the other finalist.
Thus, under fixed payments, a club will win at least 7.1 million, and the maximum 31.2 million.
On the other hand, the Barça pocketed $2.5 million for winning the Super Cup in August.
But in addition, there are the variable payments, which are enshrined 337.8 million.
This money is distributed according to the proportional value of each television market.
The Spanish market is one of the most important, and has four dedicated places.
The champion of the previous year pockets 40% of the money allocated, 30% for the second, 20% for the third and 10% for the fourth.
The other party will be paid based on the number of matches played during the edition of the year.
Nueva Rumasa provides EUR 61 million for 29.9% of SOS.
The group Nueva Rumasa listed yesterday the details of the offer to purchase of shares by which it intends to acquire a maximum of 25 to 29.9% of the capital of SOS.
A percentage which does not require it to launch a takeover bid (OPA) for all of the securities.
Specifically, Nueva Rumasa offers 1,5025 euros per share, which will be disbursed in 10 years and who will be paid at a rate of 1% per year for this report.
Yesterday, the shares of SOS have completed 1.85 euros; the supply of Nueva Rumasa therefore assesses the company 18% below the market.
According to Nueva Rumasa, the price of 1.50 euros reflects the real assessment of SOS.
The offer is conditioned by the appointment of eight of the 15 advisers.
The group of Jerez gives a period of 15 days for shareholders to indicate their interest in the sale of securities.
The CNMV assured not having been informed of this offer, although the company of Ruiz Mateos has said that she had made contact with the regulator.
If he had, the disbursement would be 611,7 million, while capital of SOS is 254,27 million.
In the meantime, SOS continues the restructuring of its direction.
In an attempt to remain outside any offers to purchase and jumping judicial of its former directors, brothers Jesús and Jaime Salazar, she announced the election of María Luis Jordá as director of internal audit.
A decision that in fact the first woman to hold a post in the food company.
It is a newly created position that will depend directly to the president of the group.
And it is not without controversy, as the company remains submerged in the legal battle for the alleged embezzlement of more than 230 million SOS to companies of Salazar.
Moreover, the possibility that in the coming months Sos reveals new misappropriation of funds cannot be ruled out.
On the credit to Salazar, the former advisers Ildefonso Ortega and Ángel Fernández Noriega (representatives of the CCM and Unicaja) said yesterday before the High Court that they had been informed of the diversion of 212 million without knowing the destination.
The NCVM authorises the takeover of exclusion of Paternina presented by Inversora Sea
The National Commission of market values (NCVM) authorized yesterday the takeover of exclusion presented by Inversora sea on Federico Paternina on 9 October last.
The oversight body explained that it authorized this operation because he understood that its terms are fitted with the standards in force and that he considered "sufficient" the content of the explanatory leaflet presented, following the changes applied on 2 December last year.
The CNMV said that the offer for the acquisition of 550 008 actions of Federico Paternina at a price of 7.65 euros per share, which is 8.95% of the capital, consisting of 6 142 786 shares admitted to trading on the stock exchanges in Madrid and Bilbao.
He further explained that 5 592 778 million shares were immobilized, and that they could in no way be transmitted before the finalisation of the offer, which he indicated that the price was set by Federico Paternina, in accordance with the provisions of the standards in force.
New tools for the expertise of cars
In these days of bad weather and accidents, car garages are not the only winners.
Every day, thousands of cars that have suffered a disaster are reduced to a garage, where an expert to assess the damage and the cost of the repair.
Every disaster is different, and the calculation of the cost of parts and labor time can be a long and complex.
To calculate the cost of a repair between 20 000 and 30 000 euros, including parts and labor can take two or three hours.
However, with the assistance of the latest computer tools, it would be a matter of minutes.
It is for this reason that almost 100% of experts use such systems.
Suppliers of services and solutions for the assessment of claims and maintenance are dedicated to the collection of information provided by the manufacturers, and then treat them and offer their customers in the form of a useful tool.
In Spain, Audatex, Solera North American group, is the company leader; 80% of the estimates are made with its products.
Other companies in competition in the field of evaluation tools and the development of information on the sector are GtMotive and Eurotax.
The work with the data provided by manufacturers is far from simple.
According to Eduardo Velázquez, commercial director of Audatex, the company in Spain with 63 manufacturers and importers, and each of them provides information in a different format.
In addition, the amount of data to treat continues to increase, so that over the last five years, more versions, variants and motorisations have been launched that over the past years.
When a new car lots on the market, these companies are at work.
It is a very difficult, because it is catalogue each thousand pieces of the vehicle and include its price.
In addition, it establishes a graphic image "smart" of each model on which you can click on the different parts of a passenger vehicle.
If it is a model sold heavily, the work can be ready in a week if the process moving very quickly.
If it is a little car sold, it can take three or four months. Currently, Audatex provides complete information on 99.2% of cars sold in Spain.
Among the most exclusive models, they have such information on the Porsche, but not the Ferrari or Lamborghini.
On the vehicles in circulation, the figure exceeds 99%.
To perform the work of documentation and development of databases, Audatex has eight centres around the world (in Spain, France, Germany, the United States, Brazil, Mexico, China and Japan), and each of them is specialized in certain brands.
The national headquarters is located in Alcobendas (Madrid).
Here, more than a hundred technicians (in general experts in mechanical) work simultaneously on three screens of computers.
Audatex invests each year 90 million to develop these databases.
Each month, 2.5 million data are recorded, and clients receive updates every two days.
The development of this enormous flow of information allows these companies to give them different uses and propose various products.
The most frequent application for the repair and maintenance, but on the country, there are also tools for the management of parts or to calculate the residual sale value or a car.
The only company that has a guide that provides information on the value of used cars in Spain is Eurotax.
Audatex does not propose in our country, but it is in the United States.
In view of the products offered by Audatex, it is easy to get an idea of the type of support it can bring to professionals in the sector.
This company offers 10 different tools, the flagship product being Audaplus, the standard solution of assessment of claims, for experts.
There are cars, motorcycles, light and heavy industrial vehicles.
In addition to the cost of parts, it takes into account the time to repair estimated by the manufacturer or the scales of paint.
This tool is bought in terms of its use, for each estimate.
The highest cost is 5.75 euros, for customers who use little, up to ten times per month.
Then, each insurance company, which conducts thousands of expertise, negotiates its price with Audatex.
Other products, such as AudaVIN, allow the identification of a vehicle and equipment with which he came out of the assembly line, only through its chassis number.
Audaglass focuses on the glasses of vehicles, and AudaSubastas is a server open to the professional sector on the Internet which enables outbid on vehicles reported wrecks.
Its statistical service is very useful for identifying trends, analyses géo-démographiques or know the common problems by brand or model.
It is possible to study, for example, how many models of a specific mark went to the garage for a breakdown or how many have suffered serious losses for a given period.
GT Motive is the only Spanish company dedicated to the development of this type of tools.
It sells, among others, Gt Estimate, which is also intended to experts and provides digital images, as well as access to official documents, price and time of the manufacturer.
Gt Motive is a company of the group Einsa, founded in 1971, as a provider of services and solutions for the assessment of claims, breakdowns or maintenance devoiture.
The guide GT evaluation is a historical reference product on the market.
The company works with 24 000 users in garages, 3 100 experts and 53 insurance companies.
Its business volume has increased at a rate of 20% per year over the past three years, and it has a turnover of EUR 10.8 million in 2008.
At the beginning of last year, she began the process of internationalization, with the establishment of an office in Paris.
For its part, Audatex was born in Germany in 1966 and is located in Spain in 1979.
According to the sources of the company, 62% of its turnover is done in Europe and in the rest of the world, and the remaining 38% in North and South America. She works with 900 insurance companies and 33 000 garages, including 3 000 are in Spain.
The global turnover of the group Solera (Audatex, Sidexa, Informex ABZ, Hollander and IMS) will amount to $557 million, 3.3% more than in 2008.
In our country, the company will collect 19.1 million euros, or 7.2 per cent more than last year.
In 2005, the group Solera was traded 1 000 million, today, its shares are valued at a total of 2 400 million.
Since 2007, it is part of the New York Stock Exchange and is part of the benchmark Standard & Poor's.
Internet auction of rugged cars
Last October, the group Solera purchased Autoonline, an Internet platform for the sale of cars, motorcycles and special vehicles evacuees.
The operation has involved a cost of 59.5 million for 85% of the company's capital, which could expand next year to 15 per cent.
The purpose of the acquisition was to provide more value-added services to its customers, with the possibility of access to a huge international market.
This service to estimate and sale is intended exclusively for professionals in the sector, such as insurance companies, experts, leasing companies, garages, the scrapped and sellers professionals who must be registered before starting to conduct operations.
This platform was created in 1996 in Germany and manages more than 650 000 operations across Europe, including 500 000 in Germany.
Among its major markets are Spain, Greece, Poland and Turkey.
There are currently more than 1500 sellers and 4,000 experts registered on the site.
It manages 3,000 announcements by day and on the Spanish market, 100 new announcements are published every day.
Under Spanish law, a car whose number of chassis has been withdrawn can no longer move, but on the other hand, some parts that are not damaged can be used as spare parts.
The vintage cars can be réenregistrées, although they have been withdrawn, after approaches complex.
Specifications of garage in four stages
With the tool Auda-taller, the company Audatex ensures that the user gets a quotation in only four steps: identify the vehicle, seek the spare parts, create a quotation and generate.
The ease of use is an essential element of these systems, especially to convince the oldest professionals who, to a greater or lesser extent, are reluctant to use of new management techniques.
The database includes 1 034 vehicles, including 666 tourism, 109, 137 motorcycles, 78 vans and trucks.
Of course, to use a computer and an Internet connection is required.
Once the model to repair identified through its chassis number, a real graphic image of the model in question is then selects the necessary part.
The user can include variables such as the price of the workforce, increases or reductions, then it can print the specifications for return to the client.
Audataller is not a tool to estimate as AudaPlus, but a catalogue of references.
The main difference between these two systems is that for garages does not include the time of Labour estimated.
The cost of using this tool for the garage is 350 euros per year, which can be the subject of a credit.
Currently, the company Audatex works for that these images are in three dimensions.
It is an innovation that mechanics are a very good eye, as it will, for example, to select a door and turn to see the inside.
